ComedySportz -- Portland's longest-running show - is fast-paced, clean, family-friendly and competitive improvisational comedy. We've played every weekend since May 28, 1993.

Two teams alternate improvised scenes, games and songs, and the audience votes for the team they like better. A referee explains the rules, calls the ComedySportz fouls, and solicits suggestions from the audience to inspire every scene/game. The ref is our secret weapon - the ref keeps it moving and keeps it clean.

ComedySportz is 100 percent family and business friendly. It's a show that entertains everyone with offending anyone - our regular show audiences features bachelor parties, church groups, senior citizens, teenagers, kids and adults at the same time.

company_description:
Starting out in 2001 as Classic Catering, Dean & Debbie Young have pleased many clients over the years with their culinary and event planning talents; always going above and beyond to make everyone happy. In 2006, they opened their first special events venue, Gatherings, along with Jim & Cheryl Cox. 
In 2008, Monterey Beach Weddings was born to create a "whole" package for our Gatherings couples. In 2010, the team was able to acquire The Perry House in Monterey and has beautifully restored it as a special events facility.
The company continued to grow with us purchasing the Perry House, our beautiful venue that offers beautiful views of the Bay and a great proximity to downtown Monterey. 
In 2016, another great opportunity came with us working with the National Trust for Historic Preservation on a New Vision for the historic Cooper Molera Adobe property right in downtown Monterey. With a lot of hard work, we started to lease the newly renovated Barns at Cooper Molera, holding our first event in July of 2018! 
Yes, another opportunity presented itself as we became the proud leaseholder of what is known as the Monterey Beach House. We are looking forward to doing a few renovations on this property as well!

company_description:
WELCOME TO ILILI.

We're honored to share the cuisine and culture of Lebanon in the heart of New York City and Washington DC. Since 2007, our home in the Flatiron District has introduced the passion and generosity of the Lebanese table to hundreds of thousands of curious diners while comforting native Lebanese guests with a celebration of their homeland and values.

Owner and Executive Chef Philippe Massoud expertly crafts a sophisticated blend
of modern and traditional Lebanese cuisine drawing influences from the span of the ancient Silk Road trade routes. Flavorful herbs and spices combine to delight the palate; earthy and delicate textures emerge from innovative combinations of savory and sweet; each bite reveals a deeper story behind the birth of the Eastern Mediterranean culinary culture.

Our warm and generous hospitality drives our mission to make every guest and team member feel genuinely welcomed and fundamentally honored. We are here to share; to pass fresh pita bread and mezze amongst old friends and new; to celebrate life and its delicious bounty.

We invite you to experience our old world hospitality, timeless generosity, and tireless dedication to uncovering and sharing the rich traditions of Lebanon and the Levant.
